24/11/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Czech Republic President Vaclav Klaus made an official visit on Thursday (November 23rd) to Athens, where he met with Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis and Parliament Speaker Anna Psarouda-Benaki.
Talks focused on EU-related issues, including efforts to rewrite the European Constitution and enlarge the Union.
They also discussed ways to boost bilateral relations.
(ANA-MPA - 23/11/06)
